## <a id="0-3-1"></a> v0.3.1–alpha.3

**Release Date:** April 15, 2020


### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* You can register Cloud Foundry deployments with <%= vars.product_short %>.
You can then retrieve the registered Cloud Foundry deployments by running `pdc cloudfoundry list`.<br>
For more information, see [Register a Cloud Foundry Deployment](./using-providing.html#register-cfs).

* You can bind a service instance provisioned through <%= vars.product_short %>
to an app in a registered Cloud Foundry deployment by passing an additional flag of the form
`--app=CF-NAME/ORG-NAME/SPACE-NAME/APP-NAME` to `pdc binding create`.<br>
For more information, see
[Bind a Service Instance to an App That Runs in Cloud Foundry](./using-provisioning.html#bind-instance-to-cf).

* The Kubernetes API group for projects is now `projects.pivotal.io`.

* You can provide optional service-specific parameters when creating a new service instance or binding by using the flag
`--parameters=PARAMETERS-AS-JSON`.<br>
For more information, see
[Create a Service Instance](./using-provisioning.html#create-instance)
or [Bind a Service Instance to an App That Runs in Cloud Foundry](./using-provisioning.html#bind-instance-to-cf).

